The Yankees added more 2022 All-Stars. Catcher Jose Trevino and pitchers Nestor Cortes and Clay Holmes will make their All-Star debuts as reserves in Los Angles later this month, the Yankees announced. Yankees ace Gerrit Cole was named to his fifth All-Star game. Yankees superstar outfielders Aaron Judge and Giancarlo Stanton will both be American League starters, the MLB announced earlier this past week.